< Text>
I would like to start off talking about the bark here at the shasta park playgrounds. Bark that's on most playgrounds at most parks that do not have sand as an alternative can really play a part on a kids motivational desire  to revisit a playground. I always got splinters so that was working against my desire to go to certant parks with playgrounds that weren't the alternative being a sandy splinterless pit. For any one else that might have felt the same way be rest assured that one visit to shasta parks playground will wash away those fears for good.
1. not only is this park almost as huge as it's ever been.
2. It's also to me the one park in MANTECA that best represents the feel of being in a grassy green set of foot hills.
3. Nice walking pathway thru the park with lots of space and benches too. As well as picnic tables.
4. Lots of trees with a nice balance of shade and sun.

‚Ä¢This is a great park in Manteca and its located on Edison st. At the top northern end of powers rd. As well it neighbors the Shasta elementary school. I probably could go on for ever about cool things to do at this park alone. I will save that for another time. To make my point here is that this parks playground does not have bark nor does it have sand pit. It has recycled rubber from shoes and tires and what ever else that any one with enough prior exposure to such a rubber product might be able to identify post recycling of such rubber product. It's pretty neat. Kinda gives like an extra bounce /absorption to your each step. Like you can jump off the swings and be less worried that landing might be so harsh on your ankles as they might have ever been befor. I think that's the best addition to park playground that many have ever adapted into doing. Thanks Shasta park of Manteca for thinking out side the box on this one. Thanks Manteca parks and rec for keeping all the parks in Manteca well kept. Thanks for taking the time too read and I wish anyone that needs it a better day. Cya</Text>

<Text>Couldn't find the bathrooms if there are any. A huge expanse of grass.  Seems good for dog walking as I did see a few people walking dogs. There's a huge fenced in area with a weird pogo like structure seeming to be torn out of the ground. (Brand name: Nexus). The swings squeak so badly they sound like elephants. There's one of those old fashioned merry go round spinners that could probably use an oil up, for it's a bit slow. There's a cute baby/parent double swing where you can swing along with your child. In total there are four big kid swings, three baby swings,and two swings with big strap over type things. Unsure what to call those. There are four emoty spots where it looks like swings should go. A huge rope like jungle gym structure lies in the middle of the older kids section. Sturdy,but I recommend heavy supervision. I also probably neglected to mention the big kid and little kid playgrounds are seperate. In the kids playground they have these creepy bouncy horse things. Overall,it's a great park and I highly recommend it. Be careful,play hard,stay safe.< /Text>< Pictures>

< time>
1594080244142<//time>
<Rate>5< /Rate>< Text>
I have not been to a super cuts in a long time.  But Covid-19 changed that. The salon I have been going to for years is closed and my hair was getting quite long. My spouse noticed that the super cuts was open so I went in and made an appointment. It was wonderful getting my hair cut. Feels like a little bit of pre virus normalcy. I have now got two cuts in the Scott's Valley location. It is easy to make a same day appointment. During the week they can usually schedule you for a cut with less than a ten minute wait. The staff are friendly. The cuts are very quick, my hair is done typically in about seven minutes. The cuts are very inexpensive I think I paid 19$ and gave my stylist a 5$ tip. So 24 dollars all in. My hair looks good. It isn't the high cost salon cut that I am used to, but it is extremely good for $24 and I feel great having hair that isn't in my eyes.  Thank you to the super cuts team in Scott's Valley!<//Text>

< Review>

< review>
If you are a self wash person then this is the place to go.There must have been about 6 bays and as many vacuum spots. I bought 5 one dollar tokens. You could use cash or credit card. I had plenty of time. There is a foaming brush in addition to the wand, but I didn't need it. The only thing I might want added is an engine wash selection and a soft water rinse at the end. You will want to wipe down your car afterwards for the best results. I struggled between 4 stars and 5 stars, but used properly with a good chamois job at the end....well you can see what my 10 year old car that has never been garaged looked like. Price, ease of use, results....I had to go 5 stars.< /review>

<user_id>117315376558664984195</user_id>< Pictures>

<Rate>5</Rate>< review>
This was my first time at Regal Carlsbad. My mom & I decided to purchase our movie tickets 7 hours early, just to get good seats & it worked. We visited the concession stands to purchase our tickets. Breanne, employee, told us that you must reserve your seats & that people must be spread out in the theatre. My mom & I came back at 7pm to purchase our popcorn & drinks. I want to thank the employee, Sarah, for helping us save money on popcorn & drinks by explaining their good deals!!! The movie that we went to see was the 7:30 showing of "Nobody". When entering Theatre #12, there was two other people sitting in their seats. I was in shock of how the seats were & how much space in between the aisles. The seats are labeled in ABC order. So, my seats were G - 10 & G - 9. Our seats were 2 rows from the back wall of the theatre right in the middle. We sat down in our seats & they were so comfortable. They were recliner seats, so you can position the level of your legs and position your head too. There is a small desk that holds your drink and your snacks. A couple came and sat anywhere for a bit of time. Another couple came into the same row that the other couple was sitting in & told them that they were in their seats. The couple that sat in the wrong seats came sitting next to us. Another couple that came at a later time sat next to us also in the same row. They left one space between us. My mom was a bit confused on how come they're allowing reserved seating when people aren't sitting in the seats that they paid for? Ushers should come in and check customers' movie tickets before the movie starts to make sure they're in the correct seats.
Other than that, the movie was really really good. I reccomend watching it. Such a long review, but I just want people to know my full experience :)< /review>

< review>
As home theater equipment gets better and better, movie theaters are making the movie experience more home like with reclining chairs and menu items far beyond the popcorn and Coke of my youth. The Regal in Carlsbad does this as well as anyone in the area. The seats are comfortable and the snack bar is well stocked with a variety of junk food. To be sure, they have actual meals, but clearly on the junk food side - hey, it's a movie theater. Food is acceptable, but if you're coming to the Regal to eat, then you should be reading a review of mental hospitals and not movie theaters.< /review>

<name>Donna Martinez<//name><pictures>None</pictures><Resp>None<//Resp><user_id>101677050520988908072<//user_id>< Review>
I‚Äôve only had to purchase tickets in person here once, and it was a quick and easy process. The lobby is big and open. It doesn‚Äôt feel cluttered and overwhelming from so many displays and tables. I can‚Äôt say much about the staff because we‚Äôve only had encounters with the younger staff, and I know in first jobs they‚Äôre so worried about doing everything correctly that they forget to smile. But no big, they‚Äôve all been courteous and none have made us feel rushed. Love the small theaters, and the seats are so comfy! There are 2-3 rows at the very front and most of the theaters are about 3-4 more rows after that. There is plenty of walkway room, and the lights on the stairs make it easy to see where you‚Äôre going. Restrooms are clean and well kept. And there are enough stalls that I‚Äôve never had to wait in line - before, during or after any movie I‚Äôve watched here. Overall, I‚Äôd say this is one of my favorite places to relax every once in a while.</Review>

<response>None</response><name>Wendy McCreary<//name><Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
This is such a nice theater. Stadium seating and recliners with foot rests. Bonus that there is tons of parking at the mall and nice restaurants nearby. Pro tip, use the kiosk for tickets instead of waiting in line. Movie pass can be used at the kiosk as well as gift cards and credit cards. Also, there is assigned seating which I always like so you can get your tickets early and not have to wait forever in the theater for a good spot</review>

<username>Liz M.<//username><Review>Staff are cheerful and the place is spacious. The seats are by reservation and are the kind which recline and have a surface for your concessions.

Very cushy and comfy - I feel sometimes like I melt into their chairs.

My one complaint is that it's not easy to find the entrance. It's tucked close to the mall entrance with a small sign; there's a much larger sign visible from the street, but it'll lead you to the back of the building, and the only way around is by climbing over hedges or going through the whole mall.

<Resp>{'time': 1524696735194, 'text': 'Nancy Chapman, thank you for the feedback, and giving Regal Cinemas Carlsbad 12 a 5 star rating. We will pass this along to our Carlsbad team, and look forward to seeing you again. If you‚Äôd like our customer service team to reach out to you, please click here:  https://www.regmovies.com/About-Regal/Contact-Us ‚Äî Regal Cinemas üé• üçø'}<//Resp><user_id>108757084675550029316<//user_id><gmap_id>0x80dc7188fc169e45:0x797a65e5bea73f59<//gmap_id>< review>
Much nicer than most Regal Cinemas I've watched movies at. There's plenty of parking, easy location to find, several enjoyable restaurants nearby if you'd like to have a bite before or after.

My favorite part is the seating.  You can choose ahead of time your seat location and they have several spots for wheelchair access. The seats are recliners, which was quite comfortable... especially as I am disabled.

As for the staff, I encountered several and they were all very polite.

The only drawbacks I saw during my visit was the crazy long, long lines at the concession counter which moved very slowly.  My server seemed as if I were talking to a robot and annoyed by the couple of questions I had about their items. But when she went to get my order, she and another employee seemed to have acquired a happier personality until she returned with my order. Once I'd paid for my items, I felt rushed to leave. Unfortunately, I am disabled and can only carry my items in one hand and use my pockets for smaller items. She was young and maybe this is her first job; I can understand that. But maybe a different change of positions (i.e. ticket taker) may suit her personality better.

Overall, I had a great experience with the one exception, which I will overlook because almost all other visits there were spot on.

‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ 5 star overall rating.<//review>

Best Movie theater in San Diego area, period!

The staff was great as we were getting our popcorn. we didn't have to go through line to get our tickets,  wanna know why? Because we ordered our tickets online as they have reserved seats!  its perfect!. The building looks great and everything is brand spanking new.

The best part, RECLINING SEATS WITH A FOOD TRAY!. I was enjoying my time watching a movie, reclining and eating my popcorn, I felt like I was home or even better. The space between rows is so big that when people have to get up to the bathroom up you don't have to move a single inch. even while reclining :) .

I will be going to this theater more often, thank you Regal for not messing this one up!< /Text>

< text>
The movie theater is well maintained and clean, I usually always buy my tickets via an app and then show up and scan said tickets from my phone which is very convenient.

The concessions can take a while though, so I advise you arrive 30-40min prior to your movie starting if you're looking to get snacks.

The seats are nice and comfortable but in some theaters they are starting to show their age due to wear and tear, loose trays, etc. But nothing major.

It's located in the Carlsbad mall space close to lots of shopping and dining, making parking a bit of a pain if you don't arrive with plenty of time to spare.

Overall solid movie theater with an enjoyable atmosphere for the whole family.< /text>

<user>108757084675550029316</user><name>Nancy Chapman<//name>< Date>
1524512110005<//Date>
<rate>5< /rate><review>Much nicer than most Regal Cinemas I've watched movies at. There's plenty of parking, easy location to find, several enjoyable restaurants nearby if you'd like to have a bite before or after.

My favorite part is the seating.  You can choose ahead of time your seat location and they have several spots for wheelchair access. The seats are recliners, which was quite comfortable... especially as I am disabled.

As for the staff, I encountered several and they were all very polite.

The only drawbacks I saw during my visit was the crazy long, long lines at the concession counter which moved very slowly.  My server seemed as if I were talking to a robot and annoyed by the couple of questions I had about their items. But when she went to get my order, she and another employee seemed to have acquired a happier personality until she returned with my order. Once I'd paid for my items, I felt rushed to leave. Unfortunately, I am disabled and can only carry my items in one hand and use my pockets for smaller items. She was young and maybe this is her first job; I can understand that. But maybe a different change of positions (i.e. ticket taker) may suit her personality better.

Overall, I had a great experience with the one exception, which I will overlook because almost all other visits there were spot on.

Best Movie theater in San Diego area, period!

The staff was great as we were getting our popcorn. we didn't have to go through line to get our tickets,  wanna know why? Because we ordered our tickets online as they have reserved seats!  its perfect!. The building looks great and everything is brand spanking new.

<username>Pauline G</username>< Review>
I really like this theater. I have the ability to not only pay for my tickets online, but also choose my seats. And the only bad seats in the house are probably the ones right up front, just like most theaters. The seats themselves aren't as new as they once were but they recline and are extra wide and comfy. I would rather drive the extra miles and be comfortable than go to a regular theater these days. Plus, the cost of the tickets are not any more expensive than other Regal Cinemas that have no reclining chairs. Also, every time I've been here, the theater has been clean and the employees friendly and helpful. Can't wait to come back again!</Review>

This has become our favorite theater.  Reserved seating, reasonable prices, and the staff is extremely well-trained and friendly. I really do like this theater. However, they are understaffed at the ticket window and the concession stand. They need to hire at least 10 more people to work during the busy times. I always get fandango tickets, but I usually end up waiting another 20 minutes just to get through concessions. And now they are checking purses, which takes even longer. <date>1532393246158<//date>< Rate>
4</Rate>
<Review>Great sound and comfortable reserved seating make this theater a winner in my book. The only reason it's not 5 stars is mostly the employees. They didn't seem happy at all and didn't really care about the patrons. Just overall lack of good customer service. This was during a matinee showing so maybe they just weren't awake yet... At 1pm on a Monday. ü§î Whatever the reason, nothing about the employee attitudes made me want to come back again. Not that they were rude. They just seemed apathetic. Reminded me of Fry's electronics employees (nothing to aspire to). I can only hope this was just the summer crew and customer service will be better again once Fall hits.

My only other observation is their nice recliners are starting to look a bit run down. There are patches of missing leather/pleather coating missing from the headrests, an obvious sign of normal wear and tear.i had some of it rub off on my shirt. Didn't even notice it until someone else pointed it out. Might wanna brush your shoulders off after your movie ends, just to be safe!

Overall it's a nice theater with a little room for improvement. Hopefully they can do better next time, but if not that still won't knock it off my list of favorite places to catch a flick. < Review>
The seats are great, and that's it. The theaters are tiny and everything is overpriced. I had the worst experience I've ever had at a movie theatre 2 days ago. We went out to celebrate my fianc√©'s birthday(with our 1 year old),and waited through their ridiculous lines, bought their expensive concession items, and found our assigned seats. Right as the movie starts, an usher comes in and starts shining his light in people's faces. He then walked up to us and asked to see our ticket, so we showed it to him, and he left. He then came back and said we have the wrong tickets (to a later movie, that our son couldn't watch). We told him they must have sold us the wrong ticket because we wouldn't take our son to an R rated movie, and he left again, leaving us to think we were okay to stay.
We were wrong. Next a manager came in, shining her light in our eyes.   Right away the manager blamed us and said we needed to leave the seats, because another family had the correct tickets for the seat. My fianc√© and I were furious,needless to say. The manager made us leave and return to the lobby.  We told her we wanted a refund for our tickets and concessions. So she told us to pick a different date and time to come see the movie. We told her "We are parents of a young child, we can't just pick an exact date and time, spur of the moment, obviously. So we would rather have two tickets for whenever.  " she acted like it was impossible for her to do, and we argued a bit. Then she said she'd go speak to the GM. She came back and suddenly was able pull out a roll of free tickets and hand us two  -.-
So, in short, the manager's not a people person(and obviously a liar), the workers sell the wrong tickets to assigned seats, and everything is expensive. If I were you, I'd go somewhere else and save your money.<//Review>

<review>I've never had a decent experience at this theater. Go here to see every movie, look people welcome to the future! If you don't like the reserved seating than you are just doing it wrong! I love it, buy my ticket hours before the showing and have basically empty theater to choose from usually, than show up right as the showing starts and no hassle just print your ticket at the machines by the customer service desk and enjoy! The food is 200% over charged but that's any movie theater so no whining at least they give you a refill on Large orders unlike Cinepolis! Have never once had a problem with fandango besides once which was user error cuz I didn't press confirm purchase. But ya really I am so glad movie theaters are catching up with the times because for someone who is an avid movie goer this makes life easy! now just make your food cheaper please!< /text>

<Resp>None</Resp>< text>
Regal Carlsbad is the love child of Cinepolis La Costa and Regal Oceanside. It‚Äôs got the lounging chairs, reserved seating and space of Cinepolis, but is more affordable with the more normal amenities of what people are more used to of a theater more than 3 years old.

Don‚Äôt get me wrong, when I go to Cinepolis it‚Äôs for cocktails, maybe some gastropub type food and a solid movie experience that is all you get what you pay for, but sometimes I don‚Äôt want to spend so much and don‚Äôt mind seeing a less than sold out matinee show, alone or whatever.

It‚Äôs actually smaller than I expected and in a good way I didn‚Äôt realize the expansion was really more for 24 as Luna and Regal could have easily been renovated without expansion.

I like the indoor ticketing, I like the auto kiosks. I like ordering via mobile since I have VIP rewards and I think there is better quality food. I‚Äôm glad they went with thinner more paper tickets. Probably saving a ton of money off just that little change. Plenty of parking.

I don‚Äôt like the bathrooms since they are basic, the hand dryers are super loud, I really wish places would have concessions closer to the theaters, maybe even behind the security portion. I don‚Äôt even use my tickets, I just show my phone now. Call me weird, but I like the seasoning powder and wish more places would carry it. They got me sneaking in my own seasoning here.

All in all it‚Äôs a great addition that has brought something back to the area. Lets face it when Mann and other theater left everyone went with them. I also think La Costa can service all of NCounty looking for full luxury. Prices are higher, service is better, it‚Äôs a new facility, but it‚Äôs still at ‚Äúthe mall‚Äù.</text>
